Script to return Block or Tract IDs from Census tables that match

Source: R/parse_geo_main.R
parse_geo.Rd

Filters either the Block or Tract data.tables to return a list of FIPS codes that match conditions specified by the User

Universal Parameters

Usage

parse_geo(census.level = "TRACT",
                 state.census.abbr = c("NY", "MD"))

Arguments

census.level

string. data.table to parse; "BLOCK" | "TRACT"

Parameters for the Block Tract

block.census.geoid

string or vector. Vector of Block IDs (FIPS)

zcta.census.geoid

string or vector. Vector of county IDs

place.census.geoid

string or vector. Vector of census place IDs

vtd.census.geoid

string or vector. Vector of Voting District IDs

urbanrural.census.geoid

string or vector. Vector of ZCTA IDs

urbanrural.nces.geoid

string or vector. Vector of NCES Locale IDs

Optional Parameters for the Census Tract

tract.census.geoid

string or vector. Vector of Tract IDs (FIPS)

county.census.geoid

string or vector. Vector of County IDs

puma.census.geoid

string or vector. Vector of PUMA IDs

state.census.geoid

string or vector. Vector of state IDs

state.census.name

string or vector. Vector of state names

metro.census.cbsa.geoid

string or vector. Vector of cbsa IDs

metro.census.cbsa.name

string or vector. Vector of census area names

metro.census.csa.geoid

string or vector. Vector of csa IDs

metro.census.csa.name

string or vector. Vector of csa names

region.woodard.nation

string or vector. Vector of region names

region.woodard.culture

string or vector. Vector of culture labels

region.census.main

string or vector. Vector of region names

region.census.division

string or vector. Vector of subregion names

state.census.abbr

string or vector. Vector of state abbreviations

Value

a list of FIPS codes for either Tract IDs or Block IDs.

Details

Function that returns FIPS codes that match dynamic User arguments
